# Smoke Checks

- Use `scripts/smoke-test.mjs` for the smallest runnable behavior check.
- Keep smoke tests framework-free: Node stdlib, fixture folders under `reports/`, and plain assertions.
- Cover behavior through CLI and imported API when defaults or public options change.
- Add one focused assertion for non-trivial logic changes instead of creating a new test harness.
- Keep generated outputs in ignored build/report folders; do not commit fixture output.
